            <title>[LU-9668] LVM on MDT running 2.8</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9668</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just wanted to find out if there is still a concern with data corruption with using LVM snapshots for backing up the MDT (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7616&quot; title=&quot;creation of LVM snapshot on ldiskfs based MDT hangs until MDT activity/use is halted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7616&quot;&gt;LU-7616&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8071&quot; title=&quot;lvcreate --snapshot of MDT hangs in ldiskfs_journal_start_sb&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8071&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8071&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). I noticed that it&apos;s fixed in 2.9 but we&apos;re not quite there yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
